{162}  A carucate is the extent cultivated by one plough in one year and
a day (120 acres).  âVilleinsâ were the lower class of labourers, living
in the village; âbordarsâ a better class, living in cottages attached to
the Manor House, and enjoying certain privileges.  âSoc-menâ were tenants
of the lord, holding their tenures by rent or âserviceâ of various kinds;
i.e., freemen.

